Fiendish Studies						KEY:Crimson Templar ~ Fiendish Studies				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.Crimson Templar Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary																				SOURCEPAGE:p.8		DESC:As a move action,|PREVARLT:CrimsonTemplarLVL,2	DESC:As a move or swift action,|PREVARGTEQ:CrimsonTemplarLVL,2	DESC:a crimson templar can study an outsider with the evil subtype he can see. The crimson templar then gains a +%1 bonus on Bluff, Disguise, Intimidate, Knowledge, Perception, Sense Motive, Stealth, and Survival checks against that outsider, and a +%1 bonus on weapon attack rolls and weapon damage rolls against it. The DCs of crimson templar class abilities against that opponent increase by %1. A crimson templar can maintain these bonuses against|(1+(CrimsonTemplarLVL>=5)+(CrimsonTemplarLVL>=10))*2	DESC:only one evil outsider at a time;|PREVARLT:CrimsonTemplarLVL,5	DESC:two evil outsiders at a time;|PREVARGTEQ:CrimsonTemplarLVL,5|PREVARLT:CrimsonTemplarLVL,10	DESC:three evil outsiders at a time;|PREVARGTEQ:CrimsonTemplarLVL,10	DESC:these bonuses remain in effect until either the outsider is dead or the crimson templar studies a new evil outsider. If a crimson templar deals sneak attack damage to an evil outsider, he can study that target as an immediate action, allowing him to apply his fiendish studies bonuses against that target (including to the weapon damage roll).	DESC:The crimson templar can end these bonuses as a free action, allowing him to study another target.|PREVARGTEQ:CrimsonTemplarLVL,5	DESC:The bonuses from fiendish studies stack with any bonuses gained from the slayer’s studied target ability or a ranger’s favored enemy ability.
