Divine Boon							KEY:Crimson Templar ~ Divine Boon					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.Crimson Templar Class Feature.SpecialQuality																						SOURCEPAGE:p.9		DESC:At 4th level, the crimson templar gains Ragathiel’s first boon. At 7th level, he gains the second boon. At 10th level, he gains the third boon. This ability allows the crimson templar to access these boons earlier than with the Deific Obedience or Celestial Obedience feat alone; it does not grant additional uses of the boons once the character reaches the necessary Hit Dice to earn the boons normally. Ragathiel’s boons are detailed on page 21 of Chronicle of the Righteous.			ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Celestial Boon ~ Ragathiel ~ Virtuous Combat	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Celestial Boon ~ Ragathiel ~ Retribution|PREVARGTEQ:CrimsonTemplarLVL,7	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Celestial Boon ~ Ragathiel ~ Pure Soul|PREVARGTEQ:CrimsonTemplarLVL,10
Heavenly Fire						KEY:Crimson Templar ~ Heavenly Fire					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.Crimson Templar Class Feature.SpecialAttack.Supernatural																				SOURCEPAGE:p.9		DESC:The crimson templar can incinerate unaware evil foes with pure celestial flame. If the crimson templar deals sneak attack damage to a creature he has successfully used his fiendish studies ability on, the sneak attack wreathes the target in crimson fire. The target must attempt a Fortitude saving throw (DC %1). If the target fails this save, it takes an additional %2d6 points of damage. Half of this damage is fire damage, but the other half results directly from divine power and is therefore not subject to being reduced by resistance or immunity to fire-based attacks. On a successful save, the target takes the sneak attack damage as normal but does not take any of the heavenly fire damage. A crimson templar can use heavenly fire %2 times per day.|10+CrimsonTemplarLVL+CHA|CrimsonTemplarLVL
Immolate							KEY:Crimson Templar ~ Immolate					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:ClassFeatures.Crimson Templar Class Feature.SpecialAttack.Supernatural																				SOURCEPAGE:p.9		DESC:Whenever the crimson templar reduces a creature with an evil alignment to negative hit points with a sneak attack or coup de grace, the target must attempt a Fortitude saving throw (DC %1). If the target fails this save, it is entirely disintegrated, leaving behind only a trace of fine ash (as per disintegrate). If an evil target is reduced to negative hit points from the heavenly fire ability, it receives no saving throw against this effect. This ability has no effect if the target does not have an evil alignment.|10+CrimsonTemplarLVL+CHA

